      • Serialized Fields

        • flag

          java.lang.String flag
          Represents the deleted state. It has one byte in size. "0" implies valid record, "1" implies deleted record.

          DBSchema.VALID_RECORD, DBSchema.DELETED_RECORD

        • name

          java.lang.String name
          Represents the name of the client company. It has 32 bytes in length.
          See Also:
          DBSchema.SUBCONTRACTOR_NAME_LENGTH

        • location

          java.lang.String location
          Represents the geographical location of the client company. It has 64 bytes in length.
          See Also:
          DBSchema.CITY_LENGTH

        • specialties

          java.lang.String specialties
          Represents the type of home improvement craftsmanship the client company provides. It has 64 bytes in length.
          See Also:
          DBSchema.TYPES_OF_WORK_PERFORMED_LENGTH

        • size

          java.lang.String size
          Represents the company size in workforce. It has 6 bytes in length.
          See Also:
          DBSchema.NUMBER_OF_STAFF_IN_ORGANIZATION_LENGTH

        • rate

          java.lang.String rate
          Represents the hourly charge rate of the client company. It has 8 bytes in length.
          See Also:
          DBSchema.HOURLY_CHARGE_LENGTH

        • owner

          java.lang.String owner
          Represents the identification of a customer that booked a contract with a client company. It has 8 bytes in length. It has only numeric digits.
          See Also:
          DBSchema.CUSTOMER_HOLDING_THIS_RECORD_LENGTH
